        <p>I'm Alan Quirk, a freelance web developer based in Australia working with small businesses, agencies and online stores worldwide. I build clean, fast websites and help keep them running smoothly.</p>
        <a href="#Contact" class="btn">Get in touch</a>
    </section>

    <section class="home-do">
        <h2>What I do</h2>
        <p>I work with Shopify, WordPress (including Elementor), and Eleventy to build and maintain websites that work well and look good.</p>
        <div class="services">
            <div class="service">
                <h3>New Builds</h3>
                <p>Clean code, mobile-responsive sites built to your specifications. I'm particularly focused on Eleventy projects for clients who value fast-loading, streamlined websites.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="service">
                <h3>Redesigns & Rebuilds</h3>
                <p>Refresh an outdated site or migrate to a better platform while keeping what works and improving what doesn't.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="service">
                <h3>Fixes & Ongoing Support</h3>
                <p>Bug fixes, updates, tweaks and improvements. Available for one-off tasks or ongoing retainer work.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p>I come from a design background, so I understand how a site should look and function from the user's perspective - not just the technical side.</p>
        <p>I write quality HTML and CSS, keep things clean and maintainable, and communicate clearly throughout the project. No marketing jargon, no overpromising. Just reliable work delivered on time.</p>
        <p>I'm responsive, easy to work with, and based in Australia working with clients around the world. Whether it's a one-off build or ongoing support, I'll make sure you know exactly what's happening and when.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="home-work">
        <h2>Recent Work</h2>
        <p>Here are a few recent projects I've worked on.</p>
        <div class="project-grid">
            {% if collections.projects | length == 0 %}
                <p>No projects found.</p>
            {% else %}  
                {% for project in collections.projects | slice(0,4) %}
                    <article class="project-card">
                        <a href="{{ project.url }}">
                            <div class="project-image" style="background-image: url('{{ project.data.thumbnail }}');"></div>
                            <div class="project-info">
                                <h3>{{ project.data.title }}</h3>
                                <p>{{ project.data.description }}</p>
                            </div>
                        </a>
                    </article>
                {% endfor %}
            {% endif %}
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="Contact" class="home-contact">
        <h2>Get in touch</h2>
        <p>Have a project in mind or need help with an existing site? Send me a message and I'll get back to you promptly.</p>
        <form action="/contact" method="POST" class="contact-form">
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <label for="name">Name</label>
                    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>                    
                </li>
                <li>
                    <label for="email">Email</label>
                    <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>                    
                </li>
                <li>
                    <label for="message">Message</label>
                    <textarea id="message" name="message" rows="5" required></textarea>                    
                </li>
                <button type="submit" class="btn">Send Message</button>
            </ul>
        </form>
        
    </section>

